This includes provisioning the Kubernetes cluster, deploying the IBM Context Forge container, and preparing the base platform so that agents can securely connect to exposed tools through the MCP server.
This work will lay the foundation for future agent integrations and tool execution workflows. The setup should be environment-ready, scalable, and aligned with the expected deployment and access patterns for the MCP-based solution.
Objective
To provision and configure the MCP server infrastructure on GCP GKE using IBM Context Forge so that agents can reliably connect to tools through a secure and manageable platform.
Business Value
Enables a standardized MCP-based integration layer for agents and tools.
Provides the base runtime environment required for future agent enablement.
Reduces manual setup effort by establishing a reusable infrastructure pattern.
Supports scalable and controlled deployment in GCP.
Scope
In Scope
Provision GCP GKE Kubernetes cluster required for MCP server deployment.
Deploy IBM Context Forge container into the cluster.
Configure the farm/base environment required for MCP server operation.
Validate that the MCP server is up and reachable.
Prepare the environment for agent integration with tools.
Out of Scope
Full agent implementation.
Tool-specific business logic integration.
Production hardening unless explicitly required.
Observability/monitoring beyond basic operational readiness, unless part of the setup requirement.
Acceptance Criteria
A GCP GKE cluster is provisioned and available for MCP server deployment.
IBM Context Forge container is successfully deployed in the cluster.
MCP server components are reachable and operational in the target environment.
Required namespaces, service accounts, secrets, configs, and network access are set up as needed.
The environment is ready for agent integration with MCP-exposed tools.
Deployment steps are documented clearly enough for repeatability.
Any prerequisites, dependencies, or access requirements are identified and recorded.

